verbose_text: Both in the studies with a 12-week time horizon and in the 52-week study, the plasma levels of oestrogenic and androgenic DHEA metabolites in prasterone treated patients were elevated in relation to the baseline, but were still within the normal range for postmenopausal women [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
evidence: levels of oestrogenic and androgenic DHEA
